'''Victor Jörgen Nilsson Lindelöf''' ({{IPA|sv|ˈvɪk.tɔr ˈlɪn.dɛˌløːv|lang}}; born 17 July 1994) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|AstonVil}} club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

Lindelöf began his career in Sweden at [[Västerås SK Fotboll|Västerås SK]], making his debut in October 2009. In December 2011, he agreed to move to [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in Portugal, initially representing the club at [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|youth]] and [[S.L. Benfica B|B]] levels. After making his first-team debut in September 2013, he continued to appear for the club at B level, while also winning three [[Primeira Liga]] titles. He joined Premier League side [[Manchester United]] in July 2017, winning an EFL Cup in 2023, and also an FA Cup in 2024, before he departed the club at the end of the 2024–25 season. Following his departure from Manchester United, Lindelöf joined Aston Villa in September 2025, winning the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] in 2026.

Lindelöf has represented Sweden at [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]], and senior levels. He was a part of the winning squad of the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]]. He made his senior international debut in March 2016 and represented his country at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], [[UEFA Euro 2020]], and [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Lindelöf played for numerous [[Västerås]]-based clubs in his youth such as [[IK Franke]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Victor Nilsson Lindelöf vann årets back |trans-title=Victor Nilsson Lindelöf won defender of the year |url=http://www.ikfranke.com/News/4865639/Victor-Nilsson-Lindelof-vann-arets-back?firstRef |language=sv |publisher=IK Franke |date=22 November 2016 |access-date=24 January 2017 |archive-date=1 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220401073713/https://www.ikfranke.com/News/4865639/Victor-Nilsson-Lindelof-vann-arets-back?firstRef |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Västerås IK Fotboll|Västerås IK]] and [[Västerås SK Fotboll|Västerås SK]].<ref name="vnl">{{cite news |url=https://muss.se/2017/07/17/allt-du-behover-veta-om-victor-nilsson-lindelof/ |first=Mikael |last=Österdahl |title=Allt du behöver veta om Victor Nilsson Lindelöf |trans-title=Everything you need to know about Victor Nilsson Lindelöf |website=muss.se |language=sv |date=17 July 2017 |access-date=31 July 2020 |archive-date=22 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422015429/https://muss.se/2017/07/17/allt-du-behover-veta-om-victor-nilsson-lindelof/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Västerås SK===
In October 2009, at the age of 15, Lindelöf made his first-team debut for Västerås SK, when the team beat [[BK Forward]] 3–0 in the last round of the [[2009 Division 1 (Swedish football)|2009 Division 1 Norra]] season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vskfotboll.nu/nyhetsarkiv/?news_id=2153 |title=Har haft ett bra år i VSK |trans-title=Have had a good year in VSK |website=VSK Fotboll |language=sv |date=26 October 2009 |access-date=30 July 2020 |archive-date=22 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422015420/https://www.vskfotboll.nu/nyhetsarkiv/?news_id=2153 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the following season, he helped his team advance a step higher in the [[Swedish football league system|Swedish league system]], as they were promoted to the [[Superettan|second highest league]].<ref name="Superettan">{{cite news |url=https://www.vskfotboll.nu/nyhetsarkiv/?news_id=2635 |title=VSK Fotboll till Superettan! |trans-title=VSK Football to Superettan! |website=VSK Fotboll |language=sv |date=17 October 2010 |access-date=30 July 2020 |archive-date=22 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422015421/https://www.vskfotboll.nu/nyhetsarkiv/?news_id=2635 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2011, he travelled to England to have a trial with [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]], but they did not make an offer for him.<ref name="vnl"/>

===Benfica===
[[File:Benf-Zen 2016 (5).jpg|thumb|Lindelöf playing for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2016|left|236x236px]]

On 1 December 2011, Lindelöf agreed to join Portuguese club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in the summer of 2012,<ref name="Victor">{{cite news |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/internationell/ovrigaligor/article14017555.ab |title=Storklubb värvar svensk 17–åring |publisher=Sportbladet |date=1 December 2011 |access-date=16 July 2012 |archive-date=1 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701153654/http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/internationell/ovrigaligor/article14017555.ab |url-status=live }}</ref> and on 8 June 2015, the contract was extended until 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/42058/language/pt-PT/.aspx |title=Victor Lindelöf renova contrato |language=pt |trans-title=Victor Lindelöf renews contract |date=8 June 2015 |publisher=S.L. Benfica |access-date=9 June 2015 |archive-date=11 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611022849/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/42058/language/pt-PT/.aspx |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the 2012–13 season, he played for the [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|youth team]] and won the [[Campeonato Nacional de Juniores|Portuguese under-19 championship]].<ref name="uefa">{{cite web |url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/news/0257-0ded7df04fd7-1946c553cc1f-1000--lindelof-preparado-para-travar-bernardo-silva/ |title=Lindelöf preparado para travar Bernardo Silva |language=pt |trans-title=Lindelöf prepared to stop Bernardo Silva |date=23 June 2015 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=3 July 2015 |archive-date=4 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704210034/http://pt.uefa.com/under21/news/newsid=2260709.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 October 2013, he debuted for the first-team in a 1–0 [[Taça de Portugal|Portuguese Cup]] win against [[CD Cinfães]], playing the full match. In the 2013–14 season, he scored 2 goals in 33 matches for the [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]].<ref name="uefa"/>

In the [[2015–16 S.L. Benfica season|2015–16 season]], he returned to the first-team in a 1–0 win against [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] in the [[2015–16 Taça da Liga|Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=2016154700197020101&language=2 |title=Taça da Liga – 3ª Fase |publisher=ForaDeJogo.net |access-date=12 March 2017 |archive-date=17 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220717065928/https://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=2016154700197020101&language=2 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 February 2016, he played the entire match for Benfica in a 1–0 home win against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in the first leg of [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]'s [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|round of 16]].<ref>{{cite news |date=16 February 2016 |title=Jonas strikes late to earn Benfica narrow win |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2015763--benfica-vs-zenit/ |publisher=UEFA |access-date=19 February 2016 |archive-date=16 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216221255/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000635/match=2015763/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Four days later, he scored his first goal for Benfica, in a 3–1 [[Primeira Liga]] victory at [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]].<ref>{{cite news |date=20 February 2016 |title=Benfica: Lindelof celebra primeiro golo pela equipa principal |trans-title=Benfica: Lindelof celebrates first goal for the first team |url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga/victor-lindelof/benfica-lindelof-celebra-primeiro-golo-pela-equipa-principal |language=pt |website=Maisfutebol |access-date=22 February 2016 |archive-date=22 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222160336/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga/victor-lindelof/benfica-lindelof-celebra-primeiro-golo-pela-equipa-principal |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 May 2017, he played in the [[2017 Taça de Portugal Final|Taça de Portugal final]], which Benfica won over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] (2–1).<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abola.pt/jogodireto/index.aspx?id=251730 |title=A Bola – Jogo em direto |newspaper=A Bola |access-date=6 November 2018 |archive-date=6 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106132300/https://www.abola.pt/jogodireto/index.aspx?id=251730 |url-status=live }}</ref> By the time he was leaving Benfica he had won three Primeira Liga titles, two Taça de Portugal titles and one Taça da Liga title.{{citation needed|date=May 2021}}

===Manchester United===
====2017–18 season====
[[File:CSKA-MU 2017 (6).jpg|thumb|Lindelöf playing for [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2017|306x306px]]
On 10 June 2017, [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] announced that they had agreed a deal with Benfica to sign Lindelöf for a fee of €35&nbsp;million (with a potential €10&nbsp;million in add-ons),<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/Portals/0/Documentos/ComunicVendaLindelofJun17.pdf |title=Comunicado |trans-title=Communication |date=10 June 2017 |access-date=15 June 2017 |publisher=S.L. Benfica |language=pt }}{{Dead link|date=April 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> pending the agreement of personal terms and the player passing a medical.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reds agree transfer for Victor Lindelof |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2017/Jun/manchester-united-agrees-transfer-with-benfica-for-sweden-defender-victor-lindelof.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=10 June 2017 |access-date=10 June 2017 |archive-date=11 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611045003/http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2017/Jun/manchester-united-agrees-transfer-with-benfica-for-sweden-defender-victor-lindelof.aspx |url-status=live }}</ref> Due to a previous sell-on clause, €3 million of the transfer fee was given to former club Västerås SK, making them amongst the richest clubs in Sweden at the time.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 June 2017 |title=Miljonregn över VSK: "Fantastiskt" |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/nqRwB |access-date=29 May 2023 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |language=sv |archive-date=16 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816012339/http://www.aftonbladet.se/a/nqRwB |url-status=live }}</ref> Lindelöf passed his medical at the [[Trafford Training Centre]] on 14 June, with the Swede signing a four-year contract with the option of an extra year; Manchester United announced that the contract would begin on 1 July.<ref>{{cite news |title=UNITED COMPLETE SIGNING OF VICTOR LINDELOF |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2017/Jun/victor-lindelof-completes-move-to-manchester-united-from-benfica-on-four-year-contract.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=14 June 2017 |access-date=14 June 2017 |archive-date=14 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614215929/http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2017/Jun/victor-lindelof-completes-move-to-manchester-united-from-benfica-on-four-year-contract.aspx |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Victor Lindelof: Manchester United sign £31m Benfica defender |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40236474 |website=BBC Sport |date=14 June 2017 |access-date=14 June 2017 |archive-date=15 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615130024/http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40236474 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He made his official debut for the club against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2017 UEFA Super Cup]]; however, it was more than two months before his [[Premier League]] debut, brought on during added time against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on 14 October.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester United manager Jose Mourinho slammed by Rio Ferdinand for bringing Victor Lindelof on in the 92nd minute against Liverpool |url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/10/14/manchester-united-manager-jose-mourinho-slammed-by-rio-ferdinand-for-bringing-victor-lindelof-on-in-the-92nd-minute-against-liverpool-7000213/ |newspaper=Metro |date=14 October 2017 |access-date=21 October 2017 |archive-date=18 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218102318/https://metro.co.uk/2017/10/14/manchester-united-manager-jose-mourinho-slammed-by-rio-ferdinand-for-bringing-victor-lindelof-on-in-the-92nd-minute-against-liverpool-7000213/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He was limited to just 17 Premier League matches, starting 13 of them, due to [[José Mourinho|Jose Mourinho]]'s preference of playing a defensive partnership of [[Chris Smalling]] and [[Phil Jones (footballer, born 1992)|Phil Jones]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Voakes|first=Kris|date=17 October 2018|title=The stats that suggest Lindelof and Bailly should be Man Utd's centre back pairing|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/the-stats-that-suggest-lindelof-and-bailly-should-be-man/1dty6mi4xwrgn14x5liuz4e7ed|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208045622/https://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/the-stats-that-suggest-lindelof-and-bailly-should-be-man/1dty6mi4xwrgn14x5liuz4e7ed|archive-date=8 February 2021|access-date=3 February 2021|website=Goal.com}}</ref>

====2018–19 season====
In the 2018–19 season, Lindelöf became Mourinho's preferred centre-back and was playing more often than he did in the previous season. He played the full 90 minutes in the first match of the season on 11 August 2018 against Leicester City, which ended in a 2–1 home win.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Begley|first=Emlyn|date=11 August 2018|title=Mourinho praises Pogba after Leicester win|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45053886|url-status=live|access-date=3 February 2021|archive-date=16 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116094533/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45053886}}</ref> He further went on to start in 11 out of 13 league matches before Jose Mourinho was sacked in December 2018 and replaced with [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]].<ref name=":0" /> Lindelöf scored his first goal for Manchester United on 29 January 2019, scoring their second goal in a 2–2 league draw at home to [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Matthew |last=Henry |title=Manchester United 2–2 Burnley: Hosts rescue late point |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46955253 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2019 |access-date=30 January 2019 |archive-date=29 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190129233544/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46955253 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2019–20 season====
In September 2019, Lindelöf signed a new contract until 2024, with the option of a further year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49745989|title=Victor Lindelof: Man Utd defender signs deal to 2024 with option for further year|date=18 September 2019|website=BBC Sport|access-date=19 September 2019|archive-date=18 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918154844/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49745989|url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 December 2019, he played 90 minutes and scored his only goal in the season in a league match against Aston Villa that ended 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Stone|first=Simon|date=1 December 2019|title=Man Utd league position 'not a concern' – Solskjaer|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50534315|url-status=live|access-date=3 February 2021|archive-date=30 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130091141/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50534315}}</ref> He ended the season making 35 appearances and scoring one goal in the league, the third most in league appearances within the club that season coming behind [[Harry Maguire]] and [[David de Gea]] who both played all 38 matches, forming a defensive partnership with Maguire in the process.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Thompson|first=Gemma|date=12 February 2020|title=Harry Maguire and Victor Lindelof discuss their defensive partnership|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/harry-maguire-and-victor-lindelof-discuss-their-partnership-and-other-great-defensive-pairings|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210207165813/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/harry-maguire-and-victor-lindelof-discuss-their-partnership-and-other-great-defensive-pairings|archive-date=7 February 2021|access-date=3 February 2021|publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Thompson|first=Gemma|date=3 April 2020|title=Defensive duo Harry Maguire and Victor Lindelof discuss importance of warm weather training camp|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/defensive-duo-harry-maguire-and-victor-lindelof-discuss-their-man-utd-partnership|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127161332/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/defensive-duo-harry-maguire-and-victor-lindelof-discuss-their-man-utd-partnership|archive-date=27 January 2021|access-date=3 February 2021|publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref>

====2020–21 season====
[[File:Manchester United v Everton, 2 October 2021 (40).jpg|thumb|upright|Lindelöf playing for [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2021]]
On 20 December 2020, Lindelöf scored his first goal of the 2020–21 season in a 6–2 home win against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Matthew |last=Howarth |title=Manchester United 6–2 Leeds United: Hosts up to third after thumping win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55291044 |website=BBC Sport |date=20 December 2020 |access-date=20 December 2020 |archive-date=20 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201220164623/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55291044 |url-status=live }}</ref> He played the full 90 minutes on 2 February 2021 in Manchester United's Premier League record-equalling [[Manchester United F.C. 9–0 Southampton F.C.|9–0]] home win against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Stone|first=Simon|date=2 February 2021|title=Man Utd beat nine-man Southampton 9–0|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55806211|url-status=live|access-date=3 February 2021|archive-date=15 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815214453/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55806211}}</ref> On 26 May 2021, he played the full 120 minutes as Manchester United lost in the [[2021 UEFA Europa League final]] to [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] after a 10–11 [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] in which Lindelöf scored United's 10th penalty kick.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Villarreal-Man. United {{!}} UEFA Europa League|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029909/|access-date=27 May 2021|website=[[UEFA]]|language=en|archive-date=14 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514080725/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029909/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2022–23 season ====
Lindelöf spent the majority of the season serving as a backup to [[Lisandro Martínez]] and [[Raphaël Varane]], alongside Harry Maguire,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Foley |first=Luka |date=23 March 2023 |title=Victor Lindelof speaks on his future at Manchester United |url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2023/03/23/in-the-summer-we-will-see-what-the-best-thing-to-do-is-victor-lindelof-on-his-manchester-united-future/ |access-date=23 April 2023 |website=CaughtOffside |language=en |archive-date=23 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423185026/https://www.caughtoffside.com/2023/03/23/in-the-summer-we-will-see-what-the-best-thing-to-do-is-victor-lindelof-on-his-manchester-united-future/ |url-status=live }}</ref> until the centre-back pairing both fell injured in a 2–2 [[UEFA Europa League]] draw with [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in April.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Man Utd-Sevilla evenly poised after two late goals |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65255442 |access-date=23 April 2023 |archive-date=18 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230418042705/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65255442 |url-status=live }}</ref> Promoted to first-choice, he would play the full 120 minutes of Manchester United's [[FA Cup]] semi-final victory against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 23 April, where he scored the winning penalty in the shootout which ended 7–6 in United's favour, securing a place in the final against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Man Utd beat Brighton on penalties to reach final|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65347158|access-date=23 April 2023|date=23 April 2023|location=Wembley|last=McNulty|first=Phil|archive-date=23 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423000218/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65347158|url-status=live}}</ref> He also played the [[FA Cup Final|FA Cup-final]] against Manchester City on 3 June, which City won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Man City 2–1 Man Utd: Ilkay Gundogan's double puts City on the brink of treble with FA Cup win |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12893847/man-city-2-1-man-utd-ilkay-gundogans-double-puts-city-on-the-brink-of-treble-with-fa-cup-win |access-date=9 June 2023 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=5 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605033334/https://www.skysports.com/amp/football/news/11095/12893847/man-city-2-1-man-utd-ilkay-gundogans-double-puts-city-on-the-brink-of-treble-with-fa-cup-win |url-status=live }}</ref> At the conclusion of the season, Lindelöf was the most accurate passer in the league, with a pass completion rate of 93.1%.<ref name="Marshall 2023">{{cite web | last=Marshall | first=Adam | title=Lindelof was league's most accurate passer | website=Manchester United | date=6 June 2023 | url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/victor-lindelof-was-premier-league-most-accurate-passer-in-2022-23 | access-date=13 June 2023 | archive-date=8 June 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608010107/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/victor-lindelof-was-premier-league-most-accurate-passer-in-2022-23 | url-status=live }}</ref>

==== 2023–24 season ====
On 11 November 2023, Lindelöf scored his first goal for Manchester United since December 2020 in a 1–0 win over [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] at Old Trafford.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/38871672/man-united-clear-awkward-hurdle-tougher-tests-lie-ahead|title=Man United clear awkward hurdle, but tougher tests lie ahead|date=12 November 2023|website=ESPN}}</ref> In December 2023, Manchester United announced they triggered their option to extend Victor Lindelof's contract by a year, until July 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-30 |title=Manchester United trigger option to extend 29-year-old's contract |url=https://metro.co.uk/2023/12/30/manchester-united-extend-victor-lindelofs-contract-20043763/ |access-date=2025-03-05 |website=Metro |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2024–25 season ====
On 2 March 2025, Lindelöf missed a penalty in a fifth round [[2024–25 FA Cup|FA Cup]] penalty shootout against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. Lindelof's kick was too central, allowing Fulham to knock Manchester United out of the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3d85nrk9v9t#LiveReporting|website=BBC|title=FA Cup LIVE: Manchester United v Fulham – live stream and score updates – BBC Sport}}</ref>

In May 2025, Manchester United announced that Lindelöf would be leaving once his contract expired at the end of the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Brown |first=Matthew |title=Man Utd confirm three departures |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-confirm-departures-for-jonny-evans-victor-lindelof-christian-eriksen-at-end-of-season|publisher=Manchester United F.C.|date=25 May 2025 }}</ref>

=== Aston Villa ===
On 1 September 2025, Lindelöf joined [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-01 |title=Aston Villa announce Victor Lindelöf signing |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/september/01/villa-announce-victor-lindel-f-signing/ |access-date=2025-09-01 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> On 13 September 2025, he made his Aston Villa debut as a second-half substitute in a 0–0 away draw at [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], playing in midfield.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |title=Everton 0–0 Aston Villa: Beto misses chances in draw |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cp8jnymg55dt |access-date=2025-09-13 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> After an injury to [[Pau Torres]], with [[Tyrone Mings]] already unavailable through injury, Lindelöf started his first league game for Villa on 14 December 2025, a 3–2 victory away at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], in which he assisted [[Morgan Rogers]]' winning goal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 December 2025 |title=West Ham United v Aston Villa {{!}} 2025/2026 {{!}} Premier League |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/match/2562054/west-ham-united-vs-aston-villa?tab=match%20info |access-date=14 December 2025 |website=Premier League |language=en}}</ref> On 20 May 2026, Lindelöf started in the [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League|2026 UEFA Europa League]] final, which Aston Villa won 3–0.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Freiburg 0-3 Aston Villa: Villans cruise past German side to win first European trophy since 1982 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c893dkqjv00t |access-date=2026-05-21 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth team===
Lindelöf made his debut for the [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21 team]] on 14 October 2014, in the second leg of the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualification play-offs]] against [[France national under-21 football team|France]].{{citation needed|date=May 2021}}

Although Lindelöf was not named in the final squad for the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], on 15 June 2015 he replaced defender [[Emil Krafth]] who was ruled out of the tournament after a back injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/u21-herr/arkiv/landslag/2015/06/krafth-missar-u21-em/ |title=Krafth missar U21-EM |date=15 June 2015 |access-date=15 June 2015 |publisher=Svenskfotboll |language=sv |archive-date=17 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617170752/http://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/u21-herr/arkiv/landslag/2015/06/krafth-missar-u21-em/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut in the tournament in the first game against [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy]]. On 30 June 2015 he successfully converted Sweden's fifth and last penalty against [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal]] in a 4–3 penalty shoot-out victory in [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship Final|the final]] to become European under-21 champion.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2015383--sweden-vs-portugal/ |title=Sweden see off Portugal on penalties |date=30 June 2015 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=30 June 2015 |archive-date=29 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629173402/http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000411/match=2015383/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He was named in the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship#Team of the tournament|Team of the Tournament]].<ref name="team of the tournament">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/0257-0ded9764d24c-e93572b2d7e4-1000--the-official-under-21-team-of-the-tournament/ |title=The official Under-21 Team of the Tournament |date=1 July 2015 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=1 July 2015 |archive-date=10 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110165524/http://www.uefa.com/under21/news/newsid=2262826.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Senior team===
[[File:UEFA EURO qualifiers Sweden vs Spain 20191015 Mikel Oyarzabal and Victor Nilsson Lindelöf.jpg|thumb|left|Lindelöf (right) playing for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] in 2019]]

==== Debut ====

Lindelöf received his first call up to the senior [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] squad in March 2016 for friendlies against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] and [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.internationalsoccerteams.com/team-news/europe/hamren-names-sweden-squad-for-turkey-czech-rep-friendlies/ |title=Hamren names Sweden squad for Turkey, Czech Rep friendlies |date=18 March 2016 |publisher=internationalsoccerteams.com |access-date=21 March 2016 |archive-date=17 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170217233706/http://internationalsoccerteams.com/team-news/europe/hamren-names-sweden-squad-for-turkey-czech-rep-friendlies/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He debuted for the country in a 2–1 away loss to Turkey on 24 March 2016.<ref>{{cite news |date=24 March 2016 |title=Lindelof estreia-se pela seleção principal da Suécia com derrota |trans-title=Lindelof debuts for Sweden's main squad with defeat |url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/euro-2016/turquia/lindelof-estreia-se-pela-selecao-principal-da-suecia-com-derrota |language=pt |website=Maisfutebol |access-date=30 March 2016 |archive-date=4 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404031328/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/euro-2016/turquia/lindelof-estreia-se-pela-selecao-principal-da-suecia-com-derrota |url-status=live }}</ref>

==== UEFA Euro 2016 ====
He was selected in Sweden's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]] in France, where he started all three of their [[UEFA Euro 2016#Group E|group games]], although Sweden failed to progress to the round of 16. Lindelöf was also selected in Sweden's 35-man provisional squad for the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in Rio de Janeiro,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/u21-herr/arkiv/landslag/2016/06/ericsons-bruttotrupp-till-os/ |title=Ericsons bruttotrupp till OS – svenskfotboll.se |website=svenskfotboll.se |access-date=14 December 2016 |archive-date=18 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018180127/http://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/u21-herr/arkiv/landslag/2016/06/ericsons-bruttotrupp-till-os/ |url-status=live }}</ref> but was prevented from participating in the tournament by his club Benfica, who believed that the involvement of their players in the Olympics would harm their chances for the following season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/landslagsfotboll/herrlandslaget/article22932188.ab|title=Nilsson Lindelöf stoppas från OS|date=2 June 2016|access-date=19 July 2017|archive-date=5 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005200310/http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/landslagsfotboll/herrlandslaget/article22932188.ab|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2018 FIFA World Cup ====
Lindelöf scored his first international goal for Sweden in a 3–0 win over [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group A|2018 FIFA World Cup]] qualifier at [[Friends Arena]] in Stockholm on 10 October 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/worldcup/season=2018/matches/round=2000717/match=2017626/index.html |title=Sweden 3–0 Bulgaria |publisher=UEFA |access-date=19 July 2017 |archive-date=5 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805124438/http://www.uefa.com/worldcup/season=2018/matches/round=2000717/match=2017626/index.html |url-status=dead }}</ref>

In May 2018, he was named in Sweden's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists &#124; Goal.com|website=goal.com|access-date=23 July 2021|archive-date=30 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330205337/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|url-status=live}}</ref> Lindelöf missed the first game against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] due to illness, but was a regular starter in defense alongside fellow centre-back [[Andreas Granqvist]] for the remainder of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|title=World Cup 2018: Manchester United misfit Lindelof starring for Sweden's brilliant defence|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/are-you-watching-jose-man-utd-misfit-lindelof-starring-for/1stvavtaxjnic1k0el95nx3ktl|access-date=21 January 2021|website=Goal.com|archive-date=15 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210715133312/https://www.goal.com/en/news/are-you-watching-jose-man-utd-misfit-lindelof-starring-for/1stvavtaxjnic1k0el95nx3ktl|url-status=live}}</ref> Lindelöf and Sweden were eliminated in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Sweden vs England|quarter final]] against [[England national football team|England]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=9 July 2018|title=Sweden World Cup Fixtures, Squad, Group, Guide|url=https://www.worldsoccer.com/world-cup/sweden-world-cup-fixtures-399889|access-date=21 January 2021|website=World Soccer|archive-date=30 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030134045/https://www.worldsoccer.com/world-cup/sweden-world-cup-fixtures-399889|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== UEFA Euro 2020 ====
In March 2019, Lindelöf was called up for Sweden's [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] matches against Romania and Norway. However, he chose to withdraw from the squad, citing personal reasons, namely the birth of his first child. He was replaced by [[Anton Tinnerholm]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/vm4pzL/janne-andersson-om-lindelofs-aterbud-kan-kraftigt-dementera-det|access-date=19 March 2019|title=Janne Andersson om Lindelöfs återbud: "Kan kraftigt dementera det"|date=18 March 2019|archive-date=18 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190318220158/https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/vm4pzL/janne-andersson-om-lindelofs-aterbud-kan-kraftigt-dementera-det|url-status=live}}</ref>

He represented Sweden at [[UEFA Euro 2020]], and appeared in all four games as Sweden reached the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout phase#Sweden vs Ukraine|round of 16]] before being eliminated by [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Tungt uttåg ur EM|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/06/tungt-uttag-ur-em/|access-date=11 August 2021|website=svenskfotboll.se|date=29 June 2021 |language=sv|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709181444/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/06/tungt-uttag-ur-em/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 August 2021, Lindelöf was named as [[Andreas Granqvist]]'s successor as captain by Sweden coach [[Janne Andersson]] following Granqvist's retirement after the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Nilsson Lindelöf ny kapten för herrlandslaget|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/08/Nilsson-Lindelof-ny-kapten-for-herrlandslaget/|access-date=11 August 2021|website=www.svenskfotboll.se|date=11 August 2021 |language=sv|archive-date=11 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210811080658/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/08/nilsson-lindelof-ny-kapten-for-herrlandslaget/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Following his move to Manchester United in 2017, Lindelöf announced his engagement to his long-time girlfriend Maja Nilsson.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/manchester-united-victor-lindelof-engaged-10669145 |title=Victor Lindelof and Maja Nilsson announce their engagement in style |first=Mick |last=Gadd |date=22 June 2017 |newspaper=Daily Mirror |access-date=5 April 2018 |archive-date=19 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180519120906/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/manchester-united-victor-lindelof-engaged-10669145 |url-status=live }}</ref> They got married at the end of May 2018, in Sweden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotbollsvm/karleksforklaring-efter-brollopet-vackra-fru/|title=Fotbollsstjärnans kärleksord till hustrun Maja|website=www.expressen.se|date=6 June 2018 |access-date=16 October 2018|archive-date=16 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181016130028/https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotbollsvm/karleksforklaring-efter-brollopet-vackra-fru/|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2019, their first son was born.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-utd-victor-lindelof-latest-16058899 |title=Manchester United get Victor Lindelof boost after fixture absence |date=2 April 2019 |access-date=8 April 2019 |archive-date=8 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408081811/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-utd-victor-lindelof-latest-16058899 |url-status=live }}</ref> Their second son was born in October 2021.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.elle.se/noje/maja-nilsson-lindelof-berattar-om-namnvalet-till-andra-sonen/7966093|last=Pettersson|first=Saga|title=Maja Nilsson Lindelöf och maken Victor fick sitt andra barn i början av Oktober. Nu berättar Maja att den minsta i familjen fått ett namn-det heter sonen!|journal=Elle|location=Stockholm|date=22 October 2021|accessdate=16 March 2023|archive-date=6 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406031100/https://www.elle.se/noje/maja-nilsson-lindelof-berattar-om-namnvalet-till-andra-sonen/7966093|url-status=live}}</ref>

While in his home city in August 2020, Lindelöf witnessed the robbery of a 90-year-old woman by a man on a bike; Lindelöf chased the thief on foot and managed to catch him, holding him until the police arrived. The police later thanked Lindelöf for his "quick and wise intervention".<ref>{{cite news |first=Mike |last=Parrott |title=Victor Lindelof Saves Elderly Woman From Thief Stealing Her Bag |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/legends-funny-news-football-victor-lindelof-saves-elderly-woman-from-thief-stealing-her-bag-20200824 |website=SPORTbible |publisher=LADbible Group |date=24 August 2020 |access-date=25 August 2020 |archive-date=24 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824193118/https://www.sportbible.com/football/legends-funny-news-football-victor-lindelof-saves-elderly-woman-from-thief-stealing-her-bag-20200824 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In January 2022, while Lindelöf was playing the full 90 minutes against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] in a 3–1 win, his [[Manchester]] home was broken into by intruders whilst he was on the pitch. His wife and two children were at home but hid and were left unharmed.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Man Utd supporting Victor Lindelof and family after break-in at house during Brentford game|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12521780/man-utd-supporting-victor-lindelof-and-family-after-break-in-at-house-during-brentford-game|access-date=27 January 2022|website=Sky Sports|language=en|archive-date=27 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127115528/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12521780/man-utd-supporting-victor-lindelof-and-family-after-break-in-at-house-during-brentford-game|url-status=live}}</ref>

